Question 6.
==========
To run the program, give the following command

python c45.py

The output will be generated as follows:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Best Split using C4.5 Algorithm
================================

                OUTLOOK         TEMPERATURE     HUMIDITY        WIND
Gain            0.2467          0.0292          0.1518          0.0481
Split Info      1.5774          1.5567          1.0000          0.9852
Gain Ratio      0.1564          0.0188          0.1518          0.0488



Gain Ratio for OUTLOOK:0.1564
Gain Ratio for TEMPERATURE:0.0188
Gain Ratio for WIND:0.0488
Gain Ratio for HUMIDITY:0.1518


The first best split for Decision Tree is OUTLOOK with GainRatio=0.1564
--------------------------------------------------------------------------


GainRatio is given by the forumla:
GainRatio(X,T) = Gain(X,T)/SplitInfo(X,T)

The first best split will be selected based on the value of GainRatio. 



Question 7.
===========
To run the program, give the following command in the terminal

python nbc.py <arg1> <arg2> <arg3> <arg4>

arg1 = attribute value of Outlook
arg2 = attribute value of Temperature
arg3 = attribute value of Humidity
arg4 = attribute value of Wind

Example:
python nbc.py sunny cool high strong

Sample Output:
==============
Naive Bayes Classifier for Weather DataSet
==============================================

Conditional Probabilities for the attributes

                sunny           cool            high            strong

        YES     0.2222          0.3333          0.3333          0.3333

        NO      0.6000          0.2000          0.8000          0.6000


Best Case with YES for the attributes = 0.0053
Best Case with NO for the attributes = 0.0206


PlayTennis is NO with probability 0.0206

